22/03/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Defence Minister Dragan Sutanovac said on Saturday (March 20th) that the security situation in southern Serbia is stable.
After visiting a military training centre in Zajecar, Sutanovac said there are no major risks to security along the administrative line with Kosovo.
Sutanovac also said he is optimistic that starting next year, Serbia will have a fully professional and modern army.
(Tanjug, Beta, B92, RTS - 20/03/10)
